        <prompt>What impact did the Hamburg Massacre of 1876 have on Reconstruction?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Demonstrated the federal government's unwillingness to protect black rights</option>
            <option letter="b">Led to increased military presence in the South</option>
            <option letter="c">Resulted in new civil rights legislation</option>
            <option letter="d">Strengthened Republican control</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Hamburg Massacre, where white supremacists killed African American militia members in South Carolina, demonstrated the federal government's declining willingness to protect black rights.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>What was the "Reconstruction Constitution" in South Carolina known for?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Creating the South's most democratic state government</option>
            <option letter="b">Restricting African American rights</option>
            <option letter="c">Maintaining slavery</option>
            <option letter="d">Supporting Confederate policies</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>South Carolina's 1868 "Reconstruction Constitution" created the most democratic state government in the South, with universal male suffrage and other progressive reforms.</explanation>
    </question>
